reference: Sharyn Wragg, formerly of Australian National University
title: Moths Data
description:
Description
The moths data frame has 41 rows and 4 columns.
These data are from a study of the effect of habitat on the
densities of two species of moth (A and P).  Transects were
set across the search area.  Within transects, sections
were identified according to habitat type.

parameters.P: number of type P moths found
parameters.habitat:
a factor with levels
Bank,
Disturbed,
Lowerside,
NEsoak,
NWsoak,
SEsoak,
SWsoak,
Upperside
parameters.A: number of type A moths found
